## Markdown Site Repository Template
This is the homepage for the nsm site repository template <mono>markdown-site</mono> [[BitBucket](https://bitbucket.org/nsm-templates/basic-site), [GitHub](https://github.com/nsm-templates/basic-site), [GitLab](https://gitlab.com/nsm-templates/basic-site)]. [Nift](https://nift.cc) (aka nsm) is a cross-platform open source git-like and $\LaTeX$-like site manager coded in C++.

This website uses [Showdown](http://showdownjs.com/) to convert Markdown to HTML.

You can import (or fork and rename) the <mono>markdown-site</mono> site repository template to begin making your own website with the same design.

See [here](https://github.com/showdownjs/showdown/wiki/Showdown's-Markdown-syntax) for documentation on Showdown's Markdown syntax. Unfortunately emoji's do not seem to work, eg. :-1:.

See the [About](@pathto(about)) page for information about adding/removing pages to/from your site and modifying the content/layout of your site.

See the [FAQ](@pathtopage(faq)) page for how to import/fork this repository along with answers to other frequently asked questions.

